content:
Hi Keepers, it's Goya ☺ Really grateful I get to say a proper goodbye to you all.

Time flew by so fast... and now that it's time to part ways I'm gonna miss you guys. I'll still peek into the community every now and then to see what you're all up to and if you're having a good time!

Joining the Morimens team was such a lucky break for me. They trusted me with so much freedom and backed all my ideas to make things better for the community and players. That's what let me take some bold swings for the community's future and aim for this kinda idealistic goal—making the Morimens community a place where players feel totally at home, where they can find anything and have a blast.

Watching the community grow and improve little by little, seeing you guys actually enjoy being here, getting positive reactions when we drop new content we worked hard on—that stuff made me so genuinely happy and proud. We're all slowly getting closer to that goal that seemed pretty far away at first.

While running this community, I got SO much kindness, trust, and support from you all.

Thank you for telling me "hit me up if you need anything" when things got tough;
Thank you for backing me up and saying stuff like "Goya, thanks for everything you do for the community";
Thank you for all those cute @mentions and messages like "Goya hungry, time for food";
Thank you for jumping into all those little interactive things I designed, haha;
...

I can't write down everyone's names or everything that happened, but I'm keeping all these unexpected acts of kindness and gifts in my memory. This has been such a special chapter of my life.

Thank you, lovely Keepers. You've filled my heart completely.

I won't be here as "official staff Goya" anymore, but I'll always genuinely love you all and wish you the best. So grateful we met, thanks for everything. May the Silver Key light our path ❤.
